Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.80,0:00:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the anti-peace forces that had\Ninvaded Ctrigall have been suppressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.39,0:00:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a number of rebels have escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.39,0:00:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's believed that they're looking\Nto converge with other units.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.23,0:00:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And, so, I would like your unit's help,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.74,0:00:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Navy Captain Diethard Bougainvillea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why come to the navy and not the army?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.45,0:00:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As you may know,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this peace signing\Nis an important ceremony
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.50,0:00:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that will affect the future\Nof the entire continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.42,0:00:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to be prepared\Nfor any unexpected situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.88,0:00:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that the army special forces\Nhave disbanded,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we will be shorthanded in an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.89,0:01:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But fortunately,\Nyour unit is still fully operational.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.14,0:01:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, the navy is perfectly\Nsuited for this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.86,0:01:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With Gilbert gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.19,0:01:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to push the trouble\Non his older brother instead, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.24,0:01:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no doubt that the opposition will\Ncome to disrupt the peace negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.41,0:01:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any ideas\Nabout what they're planning to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.29,0:01:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In three days,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.38,0:01:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the completed transcontinental railroad\Nwill carry envoys and civilian Dolls
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.55,0:01:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from Distery to Gardarik\Nas a symbol of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.09,0:01:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I sense potential risks here.\NWe must avoid another war at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.39,0:01:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You are free to use any units\Nin the vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.60,0:01:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.82,0:01:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.41,0:03:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Young lady, are you sure you want me\Nto drop you off in Distery?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can resupply, I could take you\Nall the way to Leiden, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.01,0:03:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering what you've\Njust been through...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.85,0:03:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let me know if you change your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all on edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.20,0:04:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows just how important\Nthis mission must be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, our job will be to accompany\Nthis special envoy to Gardarik,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.00,0:04:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and take part in the public\Npeace treaty exchange?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.55,0:04:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Once that's over...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that will finally put an end to the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.60,0:04:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,E-- Excuse me!\NYou must be with CH Postal Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.15,0:04:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.32,0:04:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please allow me to announce\Nour upcoming schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.15,0:04:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ship departed the Port of Leiden\Nat 1100 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.41,0:04:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We will travel north up the\NRentler River via Nahahar,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,using the canals from Machtig,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.54,0:04:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which schedules us to arrive at Distery\Nin Eckstreme at 1200 hours tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.17,0:05:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We will have you and the special envoy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.50,0:05:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,board a special train\Nwhich will be waiting for you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.26,0:05:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We are taking you part of the way\Nby ship for your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.02,0:05:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't the president of your company\Ncome here with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.94,0:05:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Retiring from service as soon\Nas the war ended. What a disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.02,0:05:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And just who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,C-- Captain Bougainvillea!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Bougainvillea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the name of Violet's major?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.37,0:05:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I am his older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.21,0:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.54,0:05:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.46,0:05:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My mission is to protect you\Nuntil we reach our destination
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.13,0:05:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and ensure the signing ceremony\Nis a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.47,0:05:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the only civilian Doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.30,0:05:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.85,0:05:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're asking about Violet,\Nshe won't be coming this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.31,0:05:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.06,0:06:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is she still working as a Doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That sorry excuse for a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hold on--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.28,0:06:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she might be flawed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.03,0:06:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but she's still trying her best.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.04,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There are even people\Nshe's saved with her letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.58,0:06:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,writes wonderful letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.38,0:06:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They slip right into a person's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.34,0:06:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Her letters allow people\Nto be true to themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.61,0:06:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you make it in time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.41,0:06:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1,041 Gardarik soldiers who escaped\Nfrom the POW camp have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.50,0:07:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for traveling all this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.79,0:07:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful to you,\NBrigadier General Merkulov,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.34,0:07:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not only for saving me in Intense,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.50,0:07:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but also for rescuing me\Nfrom the POW camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.26,0:07:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Intense, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.89,0:07:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.90,0:07:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, our diversionary\Ntactics were a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The southern fools likely believe\Nwe were wiped out in Ctrigall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.66,0:07:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.24,0:07:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We will take this opportunity\Nto destroy transportation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,between the north and south,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.79,0:07:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and use the confusion to retake Intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.92,0:07:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the railroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.93,0:07:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can follow this all the way\Nto Leidenschaftlich.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This railroad also allows food\Nand resources to enter my country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings peace to the north and south.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.32,0:08:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. We won't have to fight anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.66,0:08:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be busy\Nwith all the extra work coming in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.87,0:08:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I might get to deliver\None of your letters again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.44,0:08:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.15,0:08:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.08,0:09:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope she'll be back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.21,0:09:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fires broke out\Nalong the railway yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.88,0:09:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have them check.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.01,0:09:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they've made their move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.18,0:09:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Grandezza Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.39,0:09:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the final piece to complete the\Nconnection between the north and south.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.04,0:09:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.88,0:09:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.50,0:09:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are signs of an explosion!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.35,0:10:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Send a message to the brigadier general\Nthat our infiltration was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.48,0:10:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.95,0:10:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't we moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.53,0:10:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, there was a fire nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.04,0:10:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Vandal,\Nplease let me down near that train!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.92,0:10:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My coworkers are on that train! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.38,0:10:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They've confirmed\Nat least seven fires since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.22,0:10:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They are all near the railroad,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.48,0:10:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and only getting closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.23,0:10:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-Do you think it's the anti-peace faction?\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.11,0:10:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be targeting our train next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.82,0:11:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Send out an advanced recon unit\Nto scout out the enemy along the tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.53,0:11:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.\NI will send them out right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.12,0:11:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet! What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Cattleya, where are you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.25,0:11:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What? We're going to the peace\Nsigning ceremony with Gardarik.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.09,0:11:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There were signs of explosions nearby.\NI will go with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.47,0:11:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No. You have to get back to the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.81,0:11:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,-But--!\N-What the hell are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.52,0:11:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I happened to see you on my way\Nback from my mission in Ctrigall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.32,0:11:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say Ctrigall?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.99,0:11:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,During my mission,\NI saw remnants of the Gardarik Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.53,0:11:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.70,0:11:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-Tell me everything you know.\N-Violet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.47,0:12:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,From the air, I visually confirmed traces\Nof explosions and nine smoke pillars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As I thought, their plan is to delay\Nour train and attack us directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.43,0:12:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we confirm it is safe up ahead,\Nwe will depart as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,-You should get off this train, too.\N-I can help if there's danger ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.23,0:12:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, please give me your orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.53,0:12:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still a tool\Nwho can only follow orders, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.70,0:12:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.87,0:12:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.05,0:12:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of my sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.22,0:12:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We have received a report\Nfrom Navy Captain Bougainvillea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.89,0:12:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been explosions\Naround the railroad
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,believed to be the work\Nof the anti-peace faction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.73,0:13:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to be targeting the train\Ncarrying the special envoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him he must protect the envoy\Nat all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.74,0:13:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare all forces to deploy!\NAnd contact the surrounding nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot allow this\Nto turn into another war!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.24,0:13:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Brigadier General Merkulov!\NI have a message from the advanced forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.75,0:13:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A peace envoy is aboard a special train\Nthat left from Distery,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.21,0:13:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and Isidor succeeded in infiltrating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.18,0:13:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We will attack the train\Nand set back these peace talks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.39,0:13:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an explosion at Distery Station\Nafter our departure. No casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.\NWe managed to make it out this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.65,0:13:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but keep a strict watch\Non our surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.07,0:13:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let anyone close.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.28,0:13:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think they will attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.99,0:13:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere where we slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And somewhere where it will be\Nhard to restore if it is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.21,0:13:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Grandezza Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It took ten years to build that tunnel.\NThe transcontinental railroad
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.88,0:14:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,will be out of commission for some time\Nif it is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, there are only passengers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first and second compartments\Nof the third train car.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.73,0:14:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one young male\Nin the first compartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.53,0:14:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and one middle-aged man in the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.32,0:14:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe that he is the special envoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.87,0:14:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the soldiers are stationed\Nfrom the fourth car and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. We will begin our operation now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-Go!\N-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.51,0:14:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.52,0:15:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.03,0:15:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're at the back\Nof the fourth car! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.66,0:15:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Separate them! Stop wasting time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.88,0:15:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, their plan was to separate our forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that jolt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.71,0:15:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-Violet?\N-I will bring the special envoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.64,0:15:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of you please remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.02,0:15:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a few of them towards the back.\NI also heard noises coming from the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.86,0:15:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Our remaining forces are close to zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.95,0:15:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I will go stop this train.\NYou stay and protect the people inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:15:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.08,0:16:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought. You only want orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.54,0:16:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.09,0:16:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.17,0:16:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just a tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If I ordered you to slaughter the enemy,\Nyou wouldn't hesitate to kill them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.64,0:16:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not kill anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.10,0:16:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not need a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.02,0:16:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not a tool, then what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You! The soldier maiden\Nof Leidenschaftlich.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.53,0:16:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We meet again! What happened\Nto that kid in Ctrigall after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.62,0:16:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he die a disgrace?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for you to get mad.\NNo one would mourn his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman? Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.67,0:17:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember now. I've seen that doll\Non the battlefield before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.17,0:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Battle Doll of Leidenschaftlich.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.85,0:17:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.18,0:17:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to get back the people\Nand things you've taken from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.15,0:17:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you planning on starting another war?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think the war is over?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like you know\Nwhat I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.66,0:18:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I, we both have the memories\Nof violence burned into us like scars,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will never be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.83,0:18:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-But the war has ended in the real world.\N-It has not!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We fought dreaming for the war to end,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.30,0:18:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for the glory that was promised\Nto both the living and the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.47,0:18:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happened in reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.18,0:18:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our leaders do\Nwhatever they're told by the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.93,0:18:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the soldiers who risked their lives\Nto protect the people were scorned,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and had stones cast against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.82,0:18:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We were betrayed and abandoned\Nby everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.99,0:18:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what's wrong with wanting\Nto destroy everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.25,0:18:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not want to kill anyone anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.63,0:18:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Get her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.89,0:19:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.69,0:19:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.13,0:20:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.25,0:20:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.89,0:20:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.44,0:20:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Major?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.02,0:20:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.28,0:20:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Brigadier general! You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.54,0:20:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Diethard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.75,0:20:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot even protect yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.79,0:21:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so, how did you expect\Nto do this without killing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.63,0:21:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother Gil gave his life\Nto protect someone like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.34,0:21:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not want to kill anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.01,0:21:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The major's orders were to live, not kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.18,0:21:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What use is a battle doll\Nthat will no longer kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.73,0:21:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you weren't able\Nto protect Gilbert!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You killed Gil!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.07,0:21:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you should die, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.45,0:21:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and die!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.41,0:21:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, the major ordered me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.67,0:21:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.26,0:21:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to protect him! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.05,0:21:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to protect him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.06,0:21:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Brigadier general!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Isidor!
